1
00:00:48,759 --> 00:00:49,359
Hello everyone

2
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:50,320
I'm Lü Qingqing

3
00:00:51,119 --> 00:00:52,320
This is also my third time

4
00:00:52,320 --> 00:00:53,719
standing on the stage of the National

5
00:00:53,759 --> 00:00:55,399
Good Journalist, Good Story Competition

6
00:00:55,759 --> 00:00:56,399
First of all

7
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:57,600
please turn your attention

8
00:00:57,679 --> 00:00:58,679
to a project

9
00:00:58,799 --> 00:00:59,920
that's stunned the world

10
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,520
a Chinese mega-project,

11
00:01:01,640 --> 00:01:03,399
the Changtai Yangtze River Bridge

12
00:01:04,599 --> 00:01:05,280
What do you think? Is this topic

13
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:06,040
any good?

14
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:07,239
I think it's pretty great

15
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:08,640
I feel like new energy vehicles

16
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:09,560
would make a better topic

17
00:01:10,599 --> 00:01:11,239
New energy

18
00:01:11,519 --> 00:01:12,000
But I feel like

19
00:01:12,159 --> 00:01:13,239
since it's your third trip to Beijing

20
00:01:13,519 --> 00:01:14,400
it needs a bit more weight

21
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:16,239
Ms. Lü

22
00:01:16,319 --> 00:01:17,159
what are you up to?

23
00:01:17,599 --> 00:01:18,120
Director Li

24
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:20,640
The Good Journalist, Good Story Competition

25
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:21,439
is coming around again

26
00:01:21,560 --> 00:01:22,599
We were just debating the topic

27
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:24,640
not sure which one to pick

28
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:25,719
Still not giving up?

29
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:27,799
You just keep losing but keep fighting

30
00:01:28,079 --> 00:01:28,799
Well, my last name is Lü

31
00:01:29,519 --> 00:01:30,920
the "keep losing but keep fighting" Lü

32
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:31,760
Oh, by the way

33
00:01:32,319 --> 00:01:33,719
I've got a pretty good topic here

34
00:01:33,799 --> 00:01:35,159
The province is launching

35
00:01:35,159 --> 00:01:35,719
the Jiangsu Super League

36
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,239
Our city is holding a citywide tryout

37
00:01:37,519 --> 00:01:38,519
The tryout is this afternoon

38
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:39,439
Here's the deal

39
00:01:39,719 --> 00:01:40,760
why don't you cover this one?

40
00:01:41,599 --> 00:01:42,280
A grassroots topic

41
00:01:42,439 --> 00:01:43,599
the everyday folks' own stories

42
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:44,680
You never know

43
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:46,560
it might just beat those fancy projects

44
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:47,599
of yours

45
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:48,840
I've already arranged everything

46
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:49,959
so head over there now

47
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:07,159
Put your bag here.

48
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:11,560
Li Xiaoyong!

49
00:02:12,319 --> 00:02:13,039
You're late.

50
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:17,439
I just got off work.

51
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:18,719
And traffic was jammed.

52
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:19,639
So I...

53
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:21,520
Do you know how late you are?

54
00:02:21,879 --> 00:02:22,759
I... I know.

55
00:02:24,159 --> 00:02:24,599
I get it.

56
00:02:24,919 --> 00:02:25,240
I get it.

57
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:26,039
Usual rules.

58
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:26,879
Five laps.

59
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:27,639
Five laps?

60
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:32,280
Coach.

61
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:33,280
Coach!

62
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:34,560
I'm here, Coach!

63
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:35,360
Sorry I'm late.

64
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,560
Coach, Coach.

65
00:02:37,639 --> 00:02:38,360
Traffic was crazy.

66
00:02:38,719 --> 00:02:39,960
If I'd known it'd be this bad,

67
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:41,360
I'd have taken my scooter.

68
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:43,400
Cut the nonsense.

69
00:02:44,039 --> 00:02:44,639
Usual rules.

70
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:45,639
Five laps.

71
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:46,759
You got it.

72
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,280
Oh, you guys are all here.

73
00:02:50,719 --> 00:02:51,680
Hurry up.

74
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:52,400
Go run.

75
00:02:52,439 --> 00:02:52,960
Come on, move it.

76
00:02:53,199 --> 00:02:54,159
When did you guys get here?

77
00:02:54,159 --> 00:02:55,360
We've already finished five laps.

78
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:55,879
Hurry up.

79
00:02:56,159 --> 00:02:56,759
Hold on.

80
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:02,240
Qingqing,

81
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:03,199
I think Director Li

82
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:04,120
is just stringing us along.

83
00:03:04,599 --> 00:03:05,280
This story topic,

84
00:03:05,319 --> 00:03:06,560
no other studio would take it.

85
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:07,319
Nobody wants it.

86
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:08,599
And football

87
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:09,960
is already a niche sport here.

88
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:11,280
And it's just a friendly match.

89
00:03:11,719 --> 00:03:12,599
No one's gonna care.

90
00:03:13,759 --> 00:03:14,280
Let's give it a shot.

91
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:15,439
What if we

92
00:03:15,439 --> 00:03:16,400
dig up something good?

93
00:03:17,719 --> 00:03:18,319
You'll see.

94
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,360
When the time comes, these tickets,

95
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,280
you couldn't even give them away.

96
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:21,039
If they win,

97
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:22,439
we'll run it as news at most.

98
00:03:22,919 --> 00:03:23,400
If they lose,

99
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:24,840
we won't promote them at all.

100
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,000
That's enough.

101
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:28,599
We're already here.

102
00:03:29,599 --> 00:03:30,520
Let's trust him this once.

103
00:04:10,879 --> 00:04:11,800
Look at this kid, so eager.

104
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:12,599
Yeah.

105
00:04:13,159 --> 00:04:14,599
Too slow.

106
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:30,680
Spread those wings!

107
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,199
He's our goalkeeper.

108
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:36,079
"Spread those wings," my foot.

109
00:04:36,439 --> 00:04:37,160
Look how chubby he is.

110
00:04:37,519 --> 00:04:38,759
Like a hen sitting on her nest.

111
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,319
He's a dad now.

112
00:04:41,959 --> 00:04:42,959
Not the same king of the kids

113
00:04:42,959 --> 00:04:43,759
as he used to be.

114
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:10,600
Oh, by the way

115
00:05:11,199 --> 00:05:12,160
push the training time

116
00:05:12,319 --> 00:05:13,199
back by an hour

117
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:15,199
They're all office workers

118
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,839
The current training time

119
00:05:17,519 --> 00:05:18,560
falls right in rush hour

120
00:05:19,199 --> 00:05:19,600
Okay

121
00:05:21,759 --> 00:05:22,199
Hello

122
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,959
Is this the Changzhou Team's training?

123
00:05:25,519 --> 00:05:26,160
We're reporters from the Changzhou

124
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,560
News and Media Center

125
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:28,319
We'd like to learn about

126
00:05:28,319 --> 00:05:29,839
the tryouts for the city league

127
00:05:29,959 --> 00:05:30,800
and your preparations

128
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:32,600
Could you give us a brief introduction?

129
00:05:33,519 --> 00:05:34,160
Coach Chang

130
00:05:34,319 --> 00:05:35,120
We've been following you

131
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:35,959
online for a while

132
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,360
who coached a former national player

133
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:39,399
Reporters

134
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:40,600
Come, come, come

135
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:42,600
Me?

136
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:44,639
I'm the team manager of the Changzhou Team

137
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:46,360
You can ask me anything

138
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:48,120
We see so many players

139
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:48,800
training on the field

140
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:50,240
How many will make the cut?

141
00:05:50,399 --> 00:05:52,319
What are the tryout criteria

142
00:05:52,399 --> 00:05:53,000
this time around?

143
00:05:54,759 --> 00:05:55,680
Criteria?

144
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:57,399
Just being able to show up here

145
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:59,600
on time after work for training

146
00:05:59,959 --> 00:06:01,240
What other criteria do we need?

147
00:06:02,439 --> 00:06:03,680
That's a bit low

148
00:06:04,079 --> 00:06:05,000
I'm not joking

149
00:06:05,079 --> 00:06:05,879
Not joking

150
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:06,600
Seriously

151
00:06:08,279 --> 00:06:10,160
So do you have any expectations?

152
00:06:10,279 --> 00:06:11,519
What's the goal for this competition?

153
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,160
No goal

154
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:13,759
It's a city friendly match

155
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,079
Just playing for fun

156
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,160
For fun

157
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:23,959
From what we just filmed,

158
00:06:24,439 --> 00:06:25,240
is there a single usable line?

159
00:06:26,199 --> 00:06:27,000
Just a bunch of guys playing.

160
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,439
Amateurs, amateur players.

161
00:06:28,439 --> 00:06:29,279
Acting so full of themselves.

162
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:31,839
Digging for a story?

163
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:33,759
Dug up a whole lot of nothing.

164
00:06:35,639 --> 00:06:36,600
I'm never trusting Old Li again.

165
00:06:36,879 --> 00:06:37,920
Calm down, calm down.

166
00:06:38,879 --> 00:06:39,839
Hurry up and get dressed.

167
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,040
I'll take you guys for some good food.

168
00:06:41,199 --> 00:06:41,680
Xiaoyong.

169
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:43,360
Hurry and change, let's go eat.

170
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,199
I'll pass.

171
00:06:44,199 --> 00:06:45,079
I still haven't finished my homework.

172
00:06:45,079 --> 00:06:45,959
It's fine, come on.

173
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,079
Xiaoyong, hurry up.

174
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,199
Let's go, let's go.

175
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:49,120
Alright, let's go.

176
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,040
Grab your stuff.

177
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:56,399
Report you.

178
00:06:56,839 --> 00:06:58,199
I'm reporting every one of you.

179
00:06:58,920 --> 00:06:59,920
You guys are really something.

180
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,680
I'm over here playing support,

181
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:03,800
and all you do is charge ahead.

182
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:04,279
You guys are...

183
00:07:07,399 --> 00:07:08,199
What brings you here?

184
00:07:08,199 --> 00:07:08,720
Sister Yan.

185
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,720
Xiaoyong came too.

186
00:07:11,079 --> 00:07:12,040
We had a tryout today.

187
00:07:12,079 --> 00:07:13,800
Coach Chang worked us all evening.

188
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:14,639
So we came to your place

189
00:07:14,759 --> 00:07:15,519
to get some warmth.

190
00:07:15,959 --> 00:07:17,079
You guys still need tryouts?

191
00:07:17,959 --> 00:07:19,079
I'm noticing Old Chang

192
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:20,600
is acting more like a big shot every day.

193
00:07:20,879 --> 00:07:22,160
He's coached you since you were kids.

194
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:22,920
How could he not know you?

195
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:23,600
Exactly.

196
00:07:24,079 --> 00:07:25,199
You're Su Xiaoxiao, right?

197
00:07:25,639 --> 00:07:26,079
I've watched you play

198
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:27,199
in lots of matches.

199
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,160
What's your name?

200
00:07:29,279 --> 00:07:30,639
Sister Yan, I'm Pangdong.

201
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:32,000
I came to give it a shot,

202
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,199
see if I can make the team.

203
00:07:33,279 --> 00:07:34,000
Whether you make it or not,

204
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,120
you've still got to eat.

205
00:07:35,319 --> 00:07:35,879
Go on, take a look.

206
00:07:35,959 --> 00:07:37,160
Whatever you want, help yourselves.

207
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:37,560
Okay.

208
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,040
Alright, sounds good.

209
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,360
Sister Yan, I'll go boil some water.

210
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,079
I'll go help out.

211
00:07:40,519 --> 00:07:40,959
I'll join too.

212
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,439
I'll make myself at home, Sister Yan.

213
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:45,560
Hold on.

214
00:07:46,759 --> 00:07:47,439
Where do you think you're going?

215
00:07:47,839 --> 00:07:48,240
Sister Yan.

216
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,879
I'm... I'm just going to help out.

217
00:07:49,959 --> 00:07:51,240
They come by all the time.

218
00:07:51,439 --> 00:07:52,600
How long has it been since you came?

219
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,759
Just sit down and wait to eat.

220
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,519
No, Sister Yan, I can do it.

221
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,120
My leg injury is completely healed.

222
00:07:57,319 --> 00:07:57,680
See?

223
00:07:57,959 --> 00:07:58,720
Nothing wrong at all.

224
00:07:58,959 --> 00:08:00,399
Doesn't Sister Yan's word count anymore?

225
00:08:01,399 --> 00:08:02,000
Go sit down.

226
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:04,680
Okay.

227
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,040
I've gotta say, you're really something.

228
00:08:13,399 --> 00:08:14,439
All this time

229
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:15,639
and you haven't come to visit us.

230
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,560
Your coach misses you a lot.

231
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:19,000
You know that?

232
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,079
What do you feel like eating today?

233
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:23,920
I'll make it for you.

234
00:08:26,879 --> 00:08:28,680
Stubborn since you were a kid.

235
00:08:28,759 --> 00:08:29,839
What do you want to eat?

236
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,160
Not saying a word?

237
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,600
The usual, then, alright?

238
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:34,559
Alright?

239
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,120
That's it, smile. So handsome.

240
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:38,919
Wait here.

241
00:08:47,519 --> 00:08:48,799
Cheers!

242
00:08:50,879 --> 00:08:51,360
I gotta say,

243
00:08:51,879 --> 00:08:53,159
getting your Provincial Games

244
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,360
champion lineup back together

245
00:08:54,519 --> 00:08:55,279
sure wasn't easy.

246
00:08:55,559 --> 00:08:56,840
The Four Little Tigers are all here.

247
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:57,639
No way.

248
00:08:57,639 --> 00:08:59,840
You guys were Provincial Games champions?

249
00:09:00,679 --> 00:09:00,960
That's awesome!

250
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:01,600
What did you think?

251
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:03,240
Do you know

252
00:09:03,279 --> 00:09:04,559
what my old nickname was?

253
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,120
What?

254
00:09:05,559 --> 00:09:07,200
Changzhou Messi.

255
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:08,679
Messi?

256
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:09,639
Let me tell you,

257
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:11,519
in all of Changzhou,

258
00:09:11,519 --> 00:09:12,879
among football players,

259
00:09:13,039 --> 00:09:14,720
hardly anyone could outrun me.

260
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:15,879
Don't believe me? Ask Big Mouth.

261
00:09:15,879 --> 00:09:16,519
Yeah.

262
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:18,159
Back then, no one could outrun him.

263
00:09:18,279 --> 00:09:18,840
Now?

264
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,039
He can't outrun anyone.

265
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:25,320
Do you guys remember back then,

266
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:26,679
that one final we played?

267
00:09:27,039 --> 00:09:28,519
Me, the iron-gate defender,

268
00:09:28,639 --> 00:09:29,879
that crucial steal I made...

269
00:09:29,879 --> 00:09:31,039
Wait, wait, wait.

270
00:09:31,039 --> 00:09:32,200
Quit bragging.

271
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,559
Sure, you made the steal,

272
00:09:34,879 --> 00:09:35,639
but

273
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,720
without that pass of mine,

274
00:09:37,879 --> 00:09:39,440
getting the ball to him,

275
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,559
would that goal have happened?

276
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:41,440
Would it?

277
00:09:41,559 --> 00:09:42,440
Wait, wait. Would it?

278
00:09:42,639 --> 00:09:43,440
That goal in the final

279
00:09:43,639 --> 00:09:44,720
was passed to me by Donglin.

280
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,960
What's that got to do with your steal?

281
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:47,559
Come on, Donglin.

282
00:09:47,559 --> 00:09:48,039
Cheers.

283
00:09:49,039 --> 00:09:49,559
Chang Yi!

284
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:55,759
Sister Yan.

285
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:56,840
After all these years,

286
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:58,320
you're still pulling that?

287
00:09:58,440 --> 00:09:59,440
You scared me to death.

288
00:09:59,559 --> 00:10:00,440
We can't let Coach Chang

289
00:10:00,639 --> 00:10:01,519
catch us drinking.

290
00:10:01,679 --> 00:10:02,240
Sister Yan,

291
00:10:02,559 --> 00:10:03,440
don't scare us like that.

292
00:10:03,559 --> 00:10:05,320
My heart just skipped a beat.

293
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:06,919
Why are you guys

294
00:10:06,919 --> 00:10:08,000
so scared of Chang Yi?

295
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:08,919
Sister Yan,

296
00:10:08,919 --> 00:10:09,799
you have no idea

297
00:10:09,799 --> 00:10:11,279
how many times he chewed us out.

298
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:13,360
How many beatings I got!

299
00:10:13,639 --> 00:10:14,840
What about you? Got beat up too?

300
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:15,559
Of course!

301
00:10:15,559 --> 00:10:15,960
And you?

302
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:16,879
You never got beat up?

303
00:10:17,799 --> 00:10:18,440
Let me tell you,

304
00:10:18,519 --> 00:10:19,399
at this table,

305
00:10:19,639 --> 00:10:20,600
there are two newcomers

306
00:10:20,639 --> 00:10:22,679
who haven't been smacked by Coach Chang.

307
00:10:23,679 --> 00:10:25,159
For this tryout,

308
00:10:25,279 --> 00:10:26,240
I hope these two

309
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:28,360
get smacked! Get smacked!

310
00:10:32,879 --> 00:10:33,720
If you ask me,

311
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:35,440
Xiaoyong's still the most impressive.

312
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:36,679
He's the one who broke

313
00:10:36,679 --> 00:10:38,000
into a pro team.

314
00:10:38,279 --> 00:10:39,399
Sure, he didn't play,

315
00:10:39,879 --> 00:10:40,720
but he still fulfilled

316
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:41,799
our childhood dream.

317
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:43,080
If it weren't for back then...

318
00:10:53,639 --> 00:10:54,159
If I hadn't gotten injured,

319
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:55,799
would I be sitting here

320
00:10:55,799 --> 00:10:57,279
drinking and chatting with you guys?

321
00:10:57,879 --> 00:10:58,720
No way.

322
00:11:00,639 --> 00:11:01,039
Brother Yong.

323
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:02,679
Honestly,

324
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,559
if I had your talent,

325
00:11:04,799 --> 00:11:05,320
I'd take the gamble too.

326
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,240
You're not just fighting for yourself.

327
00:11:07,639 --> 00:11:09,200
You're fighting for all of us.

328
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:11,440
We've played football since we were kids.

329
00:11:11,639 --> 00:11:13,440
If we don't take a shot at going pro,

330
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:15,519
we'd be letting down our childhood dream.

331
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:16,440
Yeah.

332
00:11:18,519 --> 00:11:19,679
Our childhood dream.

333
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:22,279
But when we wake up,

334
00:11:22,679 --> 00:11:23,360
we realize

335
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:25,919
we were chasing the bubbles of our youth.

336
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:26,919
Come on.

337
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:28,440
Don't say "bubbles."

338
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:29,399
I'm still living that dream.

339
00:11:29,639 --> 00:11:30,279
Hey, big bros,

340
00:11:30,679 --> 00:11:32,039
my Gaokao is coming up.

341
00:11:32,279 --> 00:11:32,879
What do you think?

342
00:11:33,399 --> 00:11:34,600
Should I go to school,

343
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,639
or keep playing football?

344
00:11:36,639 --> 00:11:38,159
Are you even an adult yet, kid?

345
00:11:38,159 --> 00:11:39,399
Drinking with us already.

346
00:11:39,879 --> 00:11:40,240
Hey...

347
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,720
Why such a double standard?

348
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:43,879
Sister Yan poured me this tea.

349
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:45,679
Here.

350
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:47,200
Pour out Sister Yan's tea.

351
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:47,799
I'll pour you some booze.

352
00:11:48,679 --> 00:11:49,159
You've got to drink some.

353
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,559
Forget it, forget it.

354
00:11:50,679 --> 00:11:51,440
Zhou Hang, Zhou Hang.

355
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:51,960
Sit down, sit down.

356
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:52,960
Stop bullying the kid.

357
00:11:53,039 --> 00:11:54,080
Listen up, all of you.

358
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:55,440
The match is starting soon.

359
00:11:55,519 --> 00:11:56,720
Train hard at the tryouts.

360
00:11:56,759 --> 00:11:57,559
Aim to all make the cut.

361
00:11:57,799 --> 00:11:58,279
And then,

362
00:11:58,279 --> 00:11:59,440
don't embarrass Coach Chang.

363
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:00,120
You hear me?

364
00:12:00,799 --> 00:12:02,240
Don't worry, Sister Yan.

365
00:12:02,519 --> 00:12:03,120
We've

366
00:12:03,519 --> 00:12:04,559
pretty much won every

367
00:12:04,559 --> 00:12:05,440
Changzhou City title there is.

368
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,960
The Provincial Games champion title,

369
00:12:07,039 --> 00:12:08,200
we've won that too.

370
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,240
What's one more?

371
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,320
Piece of cake.

372
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:12,720
We are

373
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:14,360
the champions.

374
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:15,039
Cheers!

375
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:21,759
Take a break.

376
00:12:21,919 --> 00:12:22,759
Have some fruit.

377
00:12:24,559 --> 00:12:25,240
Put it here.

378
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:26,960
Help me pick one, while you're here.

379
00:12:27,279 --> 00:12:28,399
The Russia-Ukraine situation,

380
00:12:28,879 --> 00:12:29,679
or the US-China trade war,

381
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:31,440
which one would stand out more?

382
00:12:32,159 --> 00:12:33,159
They're both okay, I guess.

383
00:12:34,039 --> 00:12:35,360
But these don't really have much

384
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,320
to do with us regular folks.

385
00:12:36,559 --> 00:12:37,080
What about this?

386
00:12:37,519 --> 00:12:38,080
Football.

387
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:39,039
Our province is launching

388
00:12:39,039 --> 00:12:39,840
a city football league.

389
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:41,639
Football's actually a good idea.

390
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,679
But first, you need to learn to curse.

391
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,759
And you've gotta curse creatively.

392
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:47,759
Do you even know football?

393
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:48,879
I remember you

394
00:12:48,879 --> 00:12:49,799
don't really watch football.

395
00:12:50,159 --> 00:12:51,279
If I don't know, I can learn.

396
00:12:51,639 --> 00:12:52,639
From that comment you just made,

397
00:12:52,919 --> 00:12:53,759
you don't sound like you know journalism either.

398
00:12:53,799 --> 00:12:54,679
Fine, fine, fine.

399
00:12:54,679 --> 00:12:55,879
I don't know journalism.

400
00:12:55,879 --> 00:12:56,759
I don't know journalism.

401
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:58,399
Honey,

402
00:13:00,559 --> 00:13:01,080
I...

403
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:02,960
I think today maybe you should

404
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:04,440
pay a bit more attention to our kid.

405
00:13:04,879 --> 00:13:05,399
Our kid...

406
00:13:05,399 --> 00:13:06,840
told me something today.

407
00:13:07,679 --> 00:13:08,320
He said

408
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:11,720
he's a left-behind child.

409
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:13,159
I'm out here every day,

410
00:13:13,639 --> 00:13:15,200
running around doing business.

411
00:13:15,799 --> 00:13:17,159
And all you think about every day

412
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:18,360
is the journalism competition.

413
00:13:18,919 --> 00:13:19,679
How about we just

414
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:20,679
forget about the award?

415
00:13:21,559 --> 00:13:22,840
What our kid needs is you.

416
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:24,639
It's really not about the award.

417
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:27,080
This is my career dream.

418
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,159
I'm listening to the voice in here.

419
00:13:32,399 --> 00:13:33,600
Okay, okay, fine, fine.

420
00:13:33,639 --> 00:13:34,559
It's the voice in there.

421
00:13:34,919 --> 00:13:35,759
Then I'll support you.

422
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:38,639
Then let me tell you about this

423
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:39,840
US-China trade thing.

424
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:40,600
This topic,

425
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,279
let's toast to our little girl.

426
00:13:42,279 --> 00:13:43,320
There's... there's no wine left.

427
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:44,120
None, none.

428
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:45,600
I'll go get some. We're out.

429
00:13:45,759 --> 00:13:46,600
I'll go get it.

430
00:13:46,919 --> 00:13:47,799
Wine, wine.

431
00:13:48,039 --> 00:13:49,240
Cheers, cheers, cheers.

432
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:53,000
Another one, another one.

433
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:55,639
It's all gone.

434
00:14:55,639 --> 00:14:56,720
You came all the way out here

435
00:14:57,759 --> 00:14:58,600
just to say

436
00:14:58,600 --> 00:14:59,440
sorry to me?

437
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:02,879
You don't owe me an apology.

438
00:15:04,559 --> 00:15:05,159
You're very brave.

439
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,039
A pro career path

440
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,720
was always a narrow bridge.

441
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:12,720
From now on, use

442
00:15:12,799 --> 00:15:13,960
the grit you had on the field

443
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:15,639
to face life.

444
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:24,840
I'm heading off, Coach.

445
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:56,440
Mom.

446
00:15:59,639 --> 00:16:00,240
Is my life

447
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:01,279
already over?

448
00:16:02,639 --> 00:16:03,639
It seems like, besides football,

449
00:16:03,639 --> 00:16:04,440
I can't do anything.

450
00:16:05,559 --> 00:16:06,679
What nonsense are you talking about?

451
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:09,120
Your life is just beginning.

452
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:11,240
Mom.

453
00:16:15,519 --> 00:16:16,000
I'm sorry.

454
00:16:17,879 --> 00:16:19,039
The person I've let down the most in my life

455
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:19,840
is you.

456
00:16:20,039 --> 00:16:20,919
Mom's just fine.

457
00:16:21,639 --> 00:16:22,559
Mom's just fine.

458
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:24,759
Things will be okay once you recover.

459
00:16:25,639 --> 00:16:26,120
Mom...

460
00:16:27,639 --> 00:16:29,080
I... I can't recover.

461
00:16:30,279 --> 00:16:31,799
I can't go pro anymore.

462
00:16:31,799 --> 00:16:33,240
I really let you down.

463
00:16:34,039 --> 00:16:34,639
Mom.

464
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:37,000
I wanted to earn big money

465
00:16:37,159 --> 00:16:38,440
and buy you a house.

466
00:16:39,039 --> 00:16:39,960
I didn't want you

467
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,879
working from dawn till dusk.

468
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:43,360
It's all right, Xiaoyong.

469
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:45,519
Mom.

470
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:14,240
Xiaoyong.

471
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:19,200
Coming.
